FBIS3-34478 "drnes027_n_94002" FBIS-NES-94-027 Document Type:Daily Report 9 Feb 1994 LEBANON Abu-Nidal Group Denies Link NC0802201894 Beirut Voice of Lebanon in Arabic 1715 GMT 8 Feb 94 NC0802201894 Beirut Voice of Lebanon Language: Arabic Article Type:BFN [Text] Fatah-the Revolutionary Council [FRC], led by Abu-Nidal, denied today that it is connected with the murder 10 days ago of a Jordanian diplomat in Beirut. In a statement released in Beirut, the movement said: We affirm that we have no connection, either closely or distantly, with the assassination of the first secretary [as heard] of the Jordanian Embassy in Lebanon. The FRC statement asserted its confidence in the Lebanese judiciary and its integrity. The statement accused various agencies and parties of being behind this well-devised scenario, as the FRC statement put it.
